A frustrated person standing in a maze constructed entirely of tangled telephone cords, USB cables, and ethernet wires, their arms raised in exasperation. The maze walls tower overhead, with dead-end paths visible stretching into the distance. Scattered throughout are vintage rotary phones, broken modems, and disconnected routers, all slightly rusted and covered in cobwebs. The color palette is muted sepia tones with pops of faded red and yellow, evoking 1950s advertisement aesthetics. The person wears period-appropriate clothing. A single open door glows warmly in the far distance, impossibly far away. Vintage style illustration with halftone dot patterns and slightly worn paper texture, reminiscent of mid-century editorial illustrations.
